%3Cp%3EBig%20Tech%20companies%20train%20their%20AI%20models%20mostly%20on%20the%20work%20of%20other%20people%2C%20like%20scientists%2C%20journalists%2C%20filmmakers%2C%20or%20artists.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20creators%20have%20long%20objected%20to%20the%20practice.%20Now%2C%20the%20US%20Copyright%20Office%20appears%20to%20have%20joined%20their%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20office%20released%20on%20Friday%20its%20latest%20in%20a%20series%20of%20reports%20exploring%20copyright%20laws%20and%20artificial%20intelligence.%20The%20report%20addresses%20whether%20the%20copyrighted%20content%20AI%20companies%20use%20to%20train%20their%20AI%20models%20qualifies%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-deepseek-ai-model-distillation-training-data-copyright-karma-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efair%20use%20doctrine%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20companies%20are%20probably%20not%20going%20to%20like%20what%20they%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20companies%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-training-data-source-solutions-openai-meta-google-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edesperate%20for%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Most%20of%20them%20believe%20that%20the%20more%20information%20a%20model%20can%20digest%2C%20the%20better%20it%20will%20be.%20But%20with%20that%20insatiable%20consumption%2C%20they%20risk%20running%20afoul%20of%20copyright%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-sarah-silverman-lawsuit-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOpen%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20faced%20a%20slew%20of%20lawsuits%20from%20creators%20who%20say%20training%20AI%20models%20on%20their%20copyrighted%20work%20without%20permission%20infringes%20on%20their%20rights.%20AI%20execs%20argue%20they%20haven't%20violated%20copyright%20laws%20because%20the%20training%20falls%20under%20fair%20use.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20US%20Copyright%20Office's%20new%20report%2C%20however%2C%20it's%20not%20that%20simple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20it%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20prejudge%20the%20result%20in%20any%20particular%20case%2C%20precedent%20supports%20the%20following%20general%20observations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20office%20said.%20%26quot%3BVarious%20uses%20of%20copyrighted%20works%20in%20AI%20training%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20transformative.%20The%20extent%20to%20which%20they%20are%20fair%2C%20however%2C%20will%20depend%20on%20what%20works%20were%20used%2C%20from%20what%20source%2C%20for%20what%20purpose%2C%20and%20with%20what%20controls%20on%20the%20outputs%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20which%20can%20affect%20the%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20office%20made%20a%20distinction%20between%20AI%20models%20for%20research%20and%20commercial%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20model%20is%20deployed%20for%20purposes%20such%20as%20analysis%20or%20research%20%E2%80%94%20the%20types%20of%20uses%20that%20are%20critical%20to%20international%20competitiveness%20%E2%80%94%20the%20outputs%20are%20unlikely%20to%20substitute%20for%20expressive%20works%20used%20in%20training%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20office%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20making%20commercial%20use%20of%20vast%20troves%20of%20copyrighted%20works%20to%20produce%20expressive%20content%20that%20competes%20with%20them%20in%20existing%20markets%2C%20especially%20where%20this%20is%20accomplished%20through%20illegal%20access%2C%20goes%20beyond%20established%20fair%20use%20boundaries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20report%2C%20the%20office%20compared%20artificial%20intelligence%20outputs%20that%20essentially%20copy%20its%20training%20materials%20to%20outputs%20with%20added%20elements%20and%20new%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20one%20end%20of%20the%20spectrum%2C%20training%20a%20model%20is%20most%20transformative%20when%20the%20purpose%20is%20to%20deploy%20it%20for%20research%2C%20or%20in%20a%20closed%20system%20that%20constrains%20it%20to%20a%20non-substitutive%20task%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20office%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20training%20a%20language%20model%20on%20a%20large%20collection%20of%20data%2C%20including%20social%20media%20posts%2C%20articles%2C%20and%20books%2C%20for%20deployment%20in%20systems%20used%20for%20content%20moderation%20does%20not%20have%20the%20same%20educational%20purpose%20as%20those%20papers%20and%20books.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraining%20an%20artificial%20intelligence%20model%20to%20create%20outputs%20%26quot%3Bsubstantially%20similar%20to%20copyrighted%20works%20in%20the%20dataset%26quot%3B%20is%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20considered%20transformative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnlike%20cases%20where%20copying%20computer%20programs%20to%20access%20their%20functional%20elements%20was%20necessary%20to%20create%20new%2C%20interoperable%20works%2C%20using%20images%20or%20sound%20recordings%20to%20train%20a%20model%20that%20generates%20similar%20expressive%20outputs%20does%20not%20merely%20remove%20a%20technical%20barrier%20to%20productive%20competition%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20office%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20such%20cases%2C%20unless%20the%20original%20work%20itself%20is%20being%20targeted%20for%20comment%20or%20parody%2C%20it%20is%20hard%20to%20see%20the%20use%20as%20transformative.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20section%2C%20the%20office%20said%20it%20rejected%20two%20%26quot%3Bcommon%20arguments%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20%26quot%3Btransformative%20nature%20of%20AI%20training.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20noted%20above%2C%20some%20argue%20that%20the%20use%20of%20copyrighted%20works%20to%20train%20AI%20models%20is%20inherently%20transformative%20because%20it%20is%20not%20for%20expressive%20purposes.%20We%20view%20this%20argument%20as%20mistaken%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20office%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNor%20do%20we%20agree%20that%20AI%20training%20is%20inherently%20transformative%20because%20it%20is%20like%20human%20learning%2C%26quot%3B%20it